
//
// tilt buzzer
//
// simple hack which shows and sounds an alarm when an accelerometer detects tilt
//
// author: @jefforulez
//

//
//  ideas code and ideas stolen from:
//
// - http://www.instructables.com/id/Play-the-French-Can-Can-Using-an-Arduino-and-Buzze/
// - http://www.arduino.cc/en/Tutorial/AccelerometerMemsic2125
//

//
// parts
//

; arduino uno rev 2
: http://arduino.cc/en/Main/arduinoBoardUno

; makershield w/ mini breadboard
: http://www.makershed.com/MakerShield_p/msms01.htm

; memsic 2125 dual-axis accelerometer
: http://www.parallax.com/tabid/768/ProductID/93/Default.aspx

; radio shack 273-059 buzzer
: http://www.radioshack.com/product/index.jsp?productId=2062397

; resistors
: 1 x 100R resistor
: 2 x 220R resistor

; various jumpers

//
// wiring
//

// leds

1. connect D12 to LED1
2. connect D13 to LED2

// buzzer

3. connect D3 to 100R resistor to radio shack 273-059 buzzer to GND

// accelorometer

4. PIN6 to 5V
5. PIN3 to GND
6. PIN2 to 220R resistor to D6 
7. PIN5 to 220R resistor to D7


